Posters that taught families to have only one child were replaced almost overnight by guidelines that describe in detail who comes into question for a second child and how to apply for the authorisation.
The city administration has sent out urban employees and volunteers for family planning to visit couples at home and to push information sheets under the doors.
She also asked to provide psychological and financial advice for those who had more than one child.
The reaction was not encouraging, said family planning representatives.
