Although officials from a small rural town outside Shanghai said that there was a recovery in the requests of couples who, after the campaign, wanted a second child, the urban districts did not report any change.
The municipality of Huinan with a population of 115,000 still receives only four to five applications per month.
Disappointed Shanghai officials say that despite the campaign, the number of births expected for 2010 in the city will still be about 165,000 -- slightly higher than in 2009, but lower than in 2008.
