About one percent of the population suffers from schizophrenia at least once in their life, and in psychiatric clinics it is treated as the second most common disease after depression.
In an acute schizophrenic psychosis, those affected can usually no longer distinguish between the inner and outer worlds, they get into an exuberant state that can lead to hallucinations, size, relationship or persecution.
