Every day, thousands of vehicles involved in an accident are dragged into the workshops, where an expert has to assess the damage caused and the cost of the repair.
No accident is the same and calculating the cost of the parts and working hours can be a long and complicated task.
The calculation of repair costs of between 20,000 and 30,000 euros by hand, including parts and working hours, may take up to two or three hours.
On the other hand, with the support of the latest information technology tools, it is a matter of minutes
That is why almost 100 % of the experts use this type of system.
Service and application providers for the assessment of accidents and repairs shall collect the information they receive from manufacturers in order to process it accordingly and to offer them to their customers in the form of a useful programme.
In Spain, Audatex, part of the American group Solera, is the market leader; 80% of all opinions are produced with their products.
The other two companies competing with the tool market for assessment and preparation of a report are GtMotive and Eurotax.
Working with the data that manufacturers make available is anything but simple.
According to Eduardo Velázquez, Sales Manager of Audatex, 63 manufacturers and importers are working together, each of them providing the information in a different format.
In addition, the volume of data to be processed is becoming larger and larger, up to the point that in the last five years more versions, variants and motorizations have been on the market than in the 15 years before.
As soon as a new car enters the market, the work begins for the companies.
It is a laborious task, for each of the thousands of vehicle parts has to be catagolated and its price entered.
In addition, each model creates an "intelligent" graphics image on which you can "click" different parts of the vehicle.
If this is a much-sold model, the work can be completed in a week if the procedure is speedy.
If it is a less common car, it can take up to three or four months. Currently, Audatex has full information at 99.2% of the cars distributed in Spain.
Among the more exclusive models, for example, they have information about the Porsche models, but not via Ferrari or Lamborghini.
With regard to the road-riding vehicle fleet, it is over 99%.
For the execution of documentation work and the production of databases, Audatex has eight centres worldwide (Spain, France, Germany, the USA, Brazil, Mexico, China and Japan) and each of them specializes in certain brands.
The national headquarters are located in Alcobendas (Madrid).
There, more than a hundred technicians (usually mechanics) work simultaneously with three computer screens.
Audatex invests 90 million euros annually in the development of these databases.
Each month they record 2.5 million data and their customers receive the updates every other day.
The development of this enormous flow of information enables companies to use it in different ways and thus offer different products.
The most common use is the use for repairs and repairs, but depending on the country, there are also tools for the management of scrap parts or for calculating the error or residual value of a car.
The only company that informs about a guide who is about the value of used cars in Spain is Eurotax.
Audatex does not offer this offer in Spain but in the United States.
With the transparency of the products offered by Audatex, you can easily get an overview of the type of support it provides to industry experts.
This company offers ten different tools, with the star of the products AudaPlus, a standard solution for handling accidents for the experts.
It includes vehicles, motorcycles and light and heavy industrial vehicles.
In addition to the cost of the parts, it contains the repair times or paint prices estimated by the manufacturer.
This tool is paid depending on the purpose of use, i.e. for each opinion.
It will be the most expensive for customers who rarely use it up to a maximum of ten times a month, namely 5.75 euros per month.
On the other hand, every insurance company that produces thousands of opinions negotiates the price with Audatex.
With other products, such as AudaVIN, you can fully identify a vehicle and the equipment with which it ran from the assembly line, using the chassis number alone.
AudaGlass deals with the vehicle discs, and AudaSubastas is an online service open to the specialist market, with which you can provide for vehicles that have been declared to be total damage.
Your statistical service is very useful in identifying trends, carrying out geodemographic analyses or in obtaining information on the variations by brand and model.
For example, one can examine how many models of a particular car brand had to go to the workshop because of breakdowns or how many of them were involved in a serious accident during a certain period.
Gt Motive is the only Spanish company dedicated to the development of this type of computer tools.
It distributes among others Gt Estimate, which is also intended for reviewers and provides digital images of the same kind, access to parts or prices and official working hours of the manufacturer.
Gt Motive is a company of the Eina Group, which was founded in 1971 as a provider of services and solutions for the assessment of damages, breakdowns and maintenance of vehicles.
The GT leader for expert opinions is a reference product on the market.
They work with 24,000 users in workshops, 3,100 experts and 53 insurance companies.
In the last three years, their business volume has increased by 20% annually and in 2008 its turnover was EUR 10.8 million.
At the beginning of last year they began to go on the international market with the opening of an office in Paris.
Audatex, on the other hand, was founded in Germany in 1966 and established in Spain in 1979.
According to the company's sources, 62% of its business is in Europe and the rest of the world, and the remaining 38% in North and South America. They work with 900 insurance companies and 33,000 workshops, 3,000 of them in Spain.
Total sales in the world of the Solera group (Audatex, Sidexa, Informex ABZ, Hollander and IMS) amount to 557 million dollars, 3.35 more than in 2008.
The company has revenue of EUR 19.1 million, 7.2% more than in the previous year.
In 2005, the Solera Group was worth $1 billion on the stock exchange and today its shares are traded at a value of $2.4 billion.
Since 2007, they have been on the New York Stock Exchange and part of the Standard & Poor's Reference Index.
Auctioning of accident cars on the Internet
Last October, the Solera Autoonline group bought a record fom on the Internet for the sale of accident vehicles and motorcycles.
This purchase meant the payment of EUR 59.5 million for 85% of the company's capital, which could increase to the remaining 15% next year.
The purpose of this purchase was to offer its customers more services and value-enhancing, with the possibility of gaining access to a huge international market.
This review and purchase service is exclusively addressed to professionals such as insurance companies, experts, car rental companies, workshops, scrap sites and car dealers, who need to be registered prior to their activities.
This platform was founded in Germany in 1996 and manages more than 650,000 operations across Europe, 500,000 of them in Germany alone.
Their main markets are Spain, Greece, Poland and Turkey.
Today, the website has more than 1,500 registered sellers and 4,000 consultants.
Each day 3,000 ads are managed and 100 new ads are added to the Spanish market every day.
According to Spanish legislation, a vehicle whose chassis number has been unregistered may no longer drive on the roads, but certain parts which are not damaged may be used as spare parts.
The cars with historical value, on the other hand, may be re-authorised even if they have been de-registered after difficult administrative procedures.
Estimate of the cost of the workshop in four steps
With the Auda-Taller tool, the company Audatex ensures that the user receives a cost estimate in just four steps: identification of the vehicle, search of the spare part, creation and creation of a cost estimate.
The easy handling of these systems is a fundamental condition, especially to convince older professionals, who are usually more or less opposed to the use of these new computer techniques.
The database includes 1,034 vehicles, 666 of which are passenger cars, 109 off-road vehicles, 137 motorcycles, 78 small hauliers and 44 trucks.
Of course, you need a computer with Internet connection to use.
After the model to be repaired has been identified using the chassis number, a graphic of the respective model appears and then the required spare part is selected.
The user can include variables such as the price for working hours, surcharges or discounts, and thereafter he can have the cost estimate printed out and pass it on to his customers.
AudaTaller, however, is not a tool for assessment such as AudaPlus, but rather a reference catalogue.
The main difference between the two systems is that the workshop-oriented approach does not include estimated working hours.
The cost of using this tool is 350 euros a year, an amount that the customer can pay without further delay.
Currently, the company Audatex is working to offer these images in three-dimensional format.
This is an innovation that car mechanics have been waiting for for a long time, as you can, for example, choose a door with it and then turn the picture completely around to look at the inside.
